******
[3] California - bat, human exposure
Date: Wed 29 Jun 2016
Source: Record Searchlight [edited]
http://www.redding.com/news/local/Police--384943051.html


A woman had a brush with a bat that tested positive for rabies.

The 64-year-old woman was scratched by the bat after she stepped on it while it was lying on the ground on Tuesday [28 Jun 2016], said Red Bluff Police.

Butte County Public Health were able to capture the bat for testing and it showed positive for rabies.

Law enforcement chalks up the bat confrontation as a "rural community public health concern."

Police say to avoid handling any live bats, as it's a good way to avoid exposure to rabies or getting scratched. If anyone comes across a dead bat it's best to place them in a plastic bag and put them in the trash.

Animal Control can be reached to handle any bat encounters.

--
