[Other articles regarding the woman and the bat indicate the bat was on the ground; she did not see it and stepped on it. It was unclear if she had on sandals or was barefoot.

In each of these reports, rabies is clearly circulating in the area. Residents should be reminded to vaccinate their pets (dogs, cats, cattle, horses, goats, and sheep). Rabies can affect any mammal. Vaccination remains a cheap and safe way to protect your animals and to protect yourself. Vaccination of your animals helps to build a barrier between the virus and yourself. - Mod.TG

